OL,3,C'Brink of famine': Why South Sudan's
OL,4,Cchildren are paying the price of war
OL,6,FThey are situated in a remote part of
OL,7,Feastern South Sudan and are among the
OL,8,Ffew places in the world designated as
OL,9,Fcategory five on the world's hunger
OL,10,Fscale. There is no category six.
OL,12,FWe're in Upper Nile State, where a
OL,13,Fchild's upper arm is the giveaway.
OL,15,FIf it's thin enough for a medic's
OL,16,Fmeasuring tape to enter the red zone,
OL,17,Fthen the boy or girl is suffering from
OL,18,Facute malnutrition.
OL,20,FThroughout our visit, we saw too much
OL,21,Fred tape.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
