OL,3,C'Brink of famine': Why South Sudan's
OL,4,Cchildren are paying the price of war
OL,6,F"We are on the brink of a famine.
OL,7,FThere is no doubt," the state
OL,8,Fgovernor, James Koang Khuol, told me
OL,9,Fbefore we left the South Sudanese
OL,10,Fcapital, Juba, to get here.
OL,12,FThe region is so remote that,
OL,13,Ftravelling from the Middle East, it
OL,14,Ftook four flights and a four-hour boat
OL,15,Fride up the White Nile to reach here.
OL,17,FThe great river bisects the country,
OL,18,Fand in the worst-hit parts of Upper
OL,19,FNile state, it is the only reliable
OL,20,Flifeline left.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
