OL,3,C'Brink of famine': Why South Sudan's
OL,4,Cchildren are paying the price of war
OL,6,FMany of the villagers are trapped
OL,7,Fbecause they're too poor to go
OL,8,Felsewhere, and if they do, they risk
OL,9,Fnot being welcome for tribal reasons.
OL,11,FSo they stay put and struggle to
OL,12,Fprovide for themselves and their
OL,13,Fchildren.
OL,15,FThere are no hospital wards full of
OL,16,Fmalnourished babies because the
OL,17,Fhospitals aren't up to providing
OL,18,Finpatient care.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
